EU and India to double trade
Given that the European Union and India are partners that mostly trade with each other, the agenda of the ninth summit meeting was also dominated by this issue, as well as all other global issues.
Today there will be a Franco-Indian summit which will deal primarily with cooperation on atomic energy.
The European Union recognises the fact that India is becoming a great democratic power that should be given a greater voice in international affairs, but member countries have not yet been able to decide whether or not to support New Delhi as a permanent member of the UN Security Council.
So we did not insist on this issue at the ninth summit held yesterday in Marseille.
French President Nicolas Sarkozy, in his capacity as President of the Union, José Manuel Barroso, President of the Commission, and Javier Solana, High Representative for Foreign Affairs, received Indian Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, with whom they agreed to double trade in five years, i.e. to increase it to EUR 100 billion.
Considering that between 2000 and 2007 trade in goods rose from 25 billion to 55 billion, this is not an overly ambitious goal.
As a result, they have legally unified the 26 bilateral civil flight agreements, so air traffic can also take off in the future.
India wants to sign a free trade agreement with the EU by the end of 2009.
Sarkozy has promised to speed up the deal.
The goal is to balance because while the EU is India’s top trading partner, New Delhi is only ninth among the EU’s partners.
The summit devoted attention to global affairs.
The situation in Afghanistan and Pakistan and terrorism, the latter condemned in all its forms by both sides, and urged the convening of a UN conference.
They urged the conclusion of the Doha Trade Round, although both sides had a role in the failure of this.
The EU has confirmed that it persists in the energy and climate programme, i.e. it would like to reduce emissions of harmful substances by at least 20% by 2020.
India also agrees on this, as well as on the need to conclude a global pact at the climate conference scheduled for next year and reduce greenhouse gas production by 50% by 2050.
They also want to curb the rise in food prices and have supported the convening of an international meeting to examine the financial crisis.
The Indian Prime Minister will travel to the French capital today, where a bilateral meeting is preparing to sign a treaty on the peaceful use of atomic energy.
In Paris, it is hoped that French companies will receive a contract worth 20 billion euros to build India’s nuclear reactors.
According to information from our news agency, the deal would last 15 years.
In Frankfurt over three hundred Italian publishers
Strong presence of Italian publishers at the Frankfurt International Book Fair.
Over three hundred Italian publishers will be present at the 60th edition of the Buchmesse, the most important international event for the exchange of rights.
The Frankfurt International Book Fair is expecting more than 7,000 exhibitors from 101 different countries who will occupy the 171,790 square meters of the Fair with over 403,000 titles on display and with Turkey as the guest of honor.
The Undersecretary at the Ministry for Cultural Heritage and Activities Francesco Maria Giro will represent the Italian Government at the inauguration ceremony of the Italian Pavilion: Italy will in fact be present institutionally with a Punto Italia - 264 square meters of exhibition space.
The meeting with the press will be held at the Room Struktur in Hall 5.0 of the Buchmesse: this will be an opportunity to present figures, trends and perspectives on the state of publishing in Italy.
According to the data, the weight of foreign author books on the total Italian production, and in particular on that for adults and children, decreases progressively.
Steve Fossett's plane found, the billionaire who disappeared a year ago
The wreckage of the plane of Steve Fossett, the billionaire who disappeared on September 3, 2007 while flying in the Nevada desert, was found.
The wreckage was found on a plateau at an altitude of 3,000 meters, in the Sierra Nevada area of Mammoth Lakes, on the border between California and Nevada.
Inside the aircraft, however, there were no human remains.
“The plane was located, we sent a team, and now we have confirmation that this is exactly what Steve Fossett was flying on the day he disappeared,” he said at a news conference.
The sheriff said no human remains were found on the plane or in the surrounding area.
The 63-year-old billionaire was presumed dead in February.
The U.S. Transportation Safety Board (NTSB) said that a few hours after the wreckage was sighted, a team of investigators was sent, which then identified the device: this is the Bellanca 8kcab, missing since September 3, 2007, when Fossett took off from Yerington in Nevada for a three-hour flight.
Yesterday, also in California, not far from the Nevada border, some of Fossett’s personal belongings were found by a couple near their home in Mammoth Lakes.
These are two documents by the name of Fossett, both issued by the Federal Aviation Administration of Illinois, cash and a sweatshirt.
Fossett's search was halted a month after his disappearance.
The billionaire had earned a place in history thanks to a long series of records.
In 2002, on his sixth attempt, he became the first man to complete a round-the-world flight on a hot air balloon: two weeks of solo flight.
Three years later, he travelled around the world by plane and non-stop.
Among his many records, he also flew at 15,445 meters above the Andes, but with a co-pilot.
Glk, the advertising you don't expect
An out-of-the-box SUV with an original design and well defined by sharp lines, wide surfaces and sharp corners.
This is, in summary, Glk the latest born among the "compact" offroads of the house of the star with which Mercedes-Benz has tried to give a breath of newness in this sector.
Precisely for its contents outside the traditional canons, the communication that will accompany the launch of the Suv Glk, available at Mercedes-Benz showrooms from next October 17, will also be unexpected and unconventional.
Thus the advertising hype that will accompany the debut of the new car will start an unprecedented mode of communication also through a futuristic campaign of 3D posters, used for the first time in Italy by an automotive brand.
A project of maxi-posting, divided into three different phases, which will dominate the central shopping street of Milan, Corso Como, until November 15.
The first phase of this new type of communication will begin with the presentation of the car in stereoscopic vision and thanks to special glasses distributed near Corso Como it will be possible to see the new SUV in almost real size and in three-dimensional format.
In fact, looking at the image you will have the impression that the car comes out of the poster.
Subsequently, through the use of the innovative Elumina8 technology, the new Glk will be illuminated at different times in all its details, and then recomposed into a single image.
Undoubtedly Mercedes with this advertisement is trying to introduce something new in the stereotypical field of automotive communication.
Will this formula be able to pique the interest of future buyers? We will see.
